"E' asciuto pazzo 'o padrone" its an album of Edoardo Bennato first published on 1992 by Virgin (reissue in 2004 by Cheyenne Records): sometimes, Bennato used the nickname of Joe Sarnataro and Blue Stuff.
Joe its a character that live in America but he's from Naples. He decide to come back to Naples with a valuable collection of musicals experiences gained into the USA - the mixture of sounds and rhythms from overseas - that influenced the traditional italian music during the 20th century.
The album lyrics, describes the denounces of corruption and malpractices.
Blues, rock'n'roll and boogie-woogie are the majors, through original songs, they trace the stylemes  of the genres that influenced the popular music of the 21th century.
